Reasoning: The paper focuses on the alignment between business and information technology with the external environment of the organizations, specifically with the customers. This involves evaluating criteria and business practices for improving the relationship with customers, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the design and application of a maturity measurement model, which could fall under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and software engineering (cs.SE).
